{"defs":{"0":[{"path":["description"],"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["enabled"],"required":true,"schema_type":"boolean"},{"path":["unit"],"schema_type":"string"}],"1":[{"path":["date"]},{"path":["interval"]},{"path":["timestamp"]}],"2":[{"path":["_then"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"then"},{"path":["_then","coordRefSys"]},{"path":["_then","featureSchema"]},{"path":["_then","featureType"]},{"path":["_then","geometry"],"required":true},{"path":["_then","id"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["_then","place"]},{"path":["_then","properties"],"required":true,"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription"],"schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","compositionCategory"],"description":"The compositionCategory property (SWE::Category) provides a term from a controlled vocabulary to specify the gross compositional character of a compound material. Composition as used here is loosely construed to include both chemical composition and petrographic composition, thus multiple values may be applied to a single rock, e.g. metaluminous and alkalic, undersaturated and basic, etc. Terms would typically include broad chemical classifications such as silicate, carbonate, ferromagnesian, oxide. However, this attribute may have different terminology for different kinds of rocks - for example sandstone petrographic classification terms (e.g. feldspathic) might be placed here.","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","consolidationDegree"],"description":"The consolidationDegree property (SWE::Category) contains a term from a controlled vocabulary that specifies the degree to which an aggregation of EarthMaterial particles is a distinct solid material. Consolidation and induration are related concepts specified by this property. They define a continuum from unconsolidated material to very hard rock. Induration is the degree to which a consolidated material is made hard, operationally determined by how difficult it is to break a piece of the material. Consolidated materials may have varying degrees of induration.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent"],"description":"The property constituent is an association between a CompoundMaterialDescription and a ConstituentPart that makes up part of the CompoundMaterial.","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"oneOf"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0"],"title":"a","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","href"],"description":"Supplies the URI to a remote resource (or resource fragment).","required":true,"schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","hreflang"],"description":"A hint indicating what the language of the result of dereferencing the link should be.","schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","length"],"schema_type":"integer","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","rel"],"description":"The type or semantics of the relation.","schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","title"],"description":"Used to label the destination of a link such that it can be used as a human-readable identifier.","schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","0","type"],"description":"A hint indicating what the media type of the result of dereferencing the link should be.","schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1"],"title":"b","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","id"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties"],"schema_type":"object","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","constituentMaterial"],"description":"The constituentMaterial property is an association between a ConstituentPart and an EarthMaterial that specifies the EarthMaterial that is forming the ConstituentPart.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","constituentParticleGeometry"],"description":"Description of geometry of individual subset of particles","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","proportion"],"description":"The proportion property (SWE::QuantityRange) reports the fraction of the whole that is formed by a ConstituentPart in a part/whole relationship. It is used for the ConstituentPart portion in a CompoundMaterial. It specifies the fraction of the EarthMaterial formed by the part (e.g., 20%, minor, dominant).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","relatedMaterial"],"description":"Specifies the ConstituentPart that is playing the target role in the MaterialRelation","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","relatedMaterial","relationship"],"description":"The property relationship:GeologicRelationshipTerm contains a term from a controlled vocabulary to describe the geologic relationship (e.g., sedimentary relation, igneous relation)."},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","relatedMaterial","sourceRole"],"description":"The property sourceRole:RelationRoleTerm contains a term that describes the role played by the source earth material part (e.g., matrix, clast, overgrowth)."},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","relatedMaterial","targetRole"],"description":"The property targetRole:RelationRoleTerm contains a term describing the role played by the target earth material part (e.g., matrix, clast, overgrowth)."},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","constituent","_oneOf","1","properties","role"],"description":"The role:ConstituentPartRoleTerm property contains a term from a controlled vocabulary that describes the role a ConstituentPart plays in a CompoundMaterial aggregation. The same EarthMaterial may occur as different ConstituentParts playing different roles within one CompoundMaterial. For example, feldspar may be present as groundmass (\u201cgroundmass\u201d is a ConstituentPart::role) and as phenocrysts (\u201cphenocryst\u201d is another ConstituentPart::role) within a single igneous rock.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","geneticCategory"],"description":"The property geneticCategory (SWE::Category) provides a term from a controlled vocabulary that represents a summary geologic history of the material. (i.e., a genetic process classifier term). Examples include igneous, sedimentary, metamorphic, shock metamorphic, volcanic, pyroclastic.","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry"],"description":"The particleGeometry:ParticleGeometryDescription contains an instance of ParticleGeometryDescription.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","aspectRatio"],"description":"The aspectRatio property (SWE::Category) contains a term from a controlled vocabulary describing the geometry of particles based on the ratios of lengths of long, intermediate and short axes of grains. It equates to sphericity in sedimentary rocks (i.e., the degree to which the shape of a particle approximates a sphere). The formal definition is \u201cA quantitative specification based on the ratio of lengths of long, intermediate and short axes of grain shape\u201d. (e.g., prolate, slightly flattened, very bladed, equant, acicular, tabular).","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","particleType"],"description":"The particleType:ParticleTypeTerm provides a term from a controlled vocabulary to specify the nature of individual particles of each constituent in an EarthMaterial aggregation, based mostly on their genesis. When applied on ParticleDescription for CompoundMaterial, it would characterise all particles in aggregate. Use this property on CompoundMaterial to distinguish rocks composed of crystals (crystalline rocks) from rocks composed of granular particles (clasts, fragments). Examples include ooliths, crystals, pore space. Constituent type is determined based on the nature of the particles, and ideally is independent of the relationship between particles in a compound material aggregation.","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","shape"],"description":"The shape property (SWE::Category) describes, &#x9;the development of crystal faces bounding particles in crystalline compound materials, and &#x9;the surface rounding of grains in sedimentary rocks. Roundness is a measure of the sharpness of the edges between surfaces bounding a particle The terms shall be a term from a controlled vocabulary and be appropriate for the kind of compound material (e.g., for crystalline rocks- euhedral, ideoblastic, subhedral, anhedral, xenoblastic; for sedimentary rocks - angular, rounded).","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size"],"description":"The property size (SWE::QuantityRange) reports the size that specifies particle grainsize. Values may be reported using absolute measurements (e.g., range, mean, median, mode, maximum).","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","constraint"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","constraint","intervals"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","constraint","significantFigures"],"schema_type":"integer"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","constraint","type"],"const":"AllowedValues"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","constraint","values"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","nilValues"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","nilValues","reason"],"description":"The reason for using the reserved value","required":true,"schema_type":"string","format":"uri"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","nilValues","value"],"description":"The reserved value itself","required":true},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","type"],"required":true,"const":"QuantityRange"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","uom"],"description":"Unit of measure used to express the value of this data component","required":true},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","uom","code"],"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","uom","href"],"schema_type":"string","format":"uri"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","uom","label"],"description":"A human readable label for the unit","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","uom","symbol"],"description":"The preferred unit symbol to use when presenting the data in a UI (use the UCUM code instead if no symbol is provided)","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","size","value"],"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","sorting"],"description":"The sorting property (SWE::Category) contains a term from a vocabulary that specifies the size distribution of particles in a CompoundMaterial. Terminology for sorting in sedimentary rocks is based on the quantitative Graphic Standard Deviation (IGSD) scheme proposed by Folk. Example for this attribute may include sedimentary terms such as well sorted and poorly sorted, or igneous terms such as porphyritic, equigranular, seriate.","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription","particleGeometry","sourceOrganism"],"description":"The sourceOrganism property is an association between a ParticleGeometryDescription and an Organism that is the source of the fossil particles (sponge spicules, bivalve shells, etc.).","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","id"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties"],"schema_type":"object","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color"],"description":"The color property (SWE::Category) is a term from a controlled vocabulary that specifies the colour of the earth material. Color schemes such as the Munsell rock and soil color schemes may be used.","schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","axisID"],"description":"Specifies the reference axis (refer to CRS axisID). The reference frame URI should also be specified unless it is inherited from parent Vector","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","codeSpace"],"description":"Name of the dictionary where the possible values for this component are listed and defined","schema_type":"string","format":"uri"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint"]},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","_oneOf"],"keyword":"oneOf"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","_oneOf","0"],"title":"Enum Values","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","_oneOf","0","values"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","_oneOf","1"],"title":"Regex Pattern","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","_oneOf","1","pattern"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","format":"regex"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","constraint","type"],"const":"AllowedTokens"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","definition"],"description":"The definition of the property whose value is provided by this component (semantic link)","schema_type":"string","format":"uri"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","description"],"description":"Human readable description of the object","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","id"],"description":"The ID of the object, referenceable using a URI fragment","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","label"],"description":"Human readable label for the object","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","nilValues"],"description":"Defines reserved values with special meaning (e.g., missing, out-of-range, etc.)"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","nilValues","reason"],"description":"The reason for using the reserved value","required":true,"schema_type":"string","format":"uri"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","nilValues","value"],"description":"The reserved value itself","required":true,"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","optional"],"description":"Specifies if the data for this component can be omitted in the datastream","schema_type":"boolean"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","referenceFrame"],"description":"Frame of reference (usually temporal or spatial) with respect to which the value of the component is expressed. A reference frame anchors a value to a real world datum.","schema_type":"string","format":"uri-reference"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","type"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string","const":"Category"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","updatable"],"description":"Specifies if the value of a data component can be updated externally (i.e., is variable)","schema_type":"boolean"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","color","value"],"description":"Inline value(s) for the component. This property is optional to enable structure to act as a schema for values provided separately (e.g., in a datastream)","schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","gbEarthMaterialDescription"],"description":"The property gbEarthMaterialDescription:EarthMaterialAbstractDescription provides a detailed earth material description of the part. This property is a stub in GeoSciML Basic as EarthMaterialAbstractDescription is abstract with subtypes defined in GeoSciML Extension.","schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","lithology"],"description":"The lithology:LithologyTerm property provides a term identifying the lithology class from a controlled vocabulary."},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","mineralName"],"description":"Name of the mineral (eg: orthoclase) or mineral family (eg: feldspar), approved by the International Mineralogical Association. (eg: http://www.mindat.org/mineralindex.php)","schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"]},{"path":["_then","properties","properties","purpose"],"description":"The purpose:DescriptionPurpose property provides a specification of the intended purpose or level of abstraction for the given EarthMaterial. The intent is the same a GeologicFeature\u2019s purpose and it shares the same vocabulary (instance, typicalNorm, definingNorm)."},{"path":["_then","time"],"ref":"1"},{"path":["_then","type"],"required":true,"const":"Feature"},{"path":["coordRefSys"]},{"path":["featureSchema"]},{"path":["featureType"]},{"path":["geometry"],"required":true},{"path":["id"]},{"path":["measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["place"]},{"path":["properties"],"required":true},{"path":["time"],"ref":"1"},{"path":["type"],"required":true,"const":"Feature"}]},"properties":[{"path":["_then"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"then"},{"path":["_then","type"],"required":true,"const":"FeatureCollection"},{"path":["_then","featureType"]},{"path":["_then","geometryDimension"],"schema_type":"integer"},{"path":["_then","featureSchema"]},{"path":["_then","coordRefSys"]},{"path":["_then","measures"],"ref":"0"},{"path":["_then","features"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array","sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"ref":"2"},{"path":["_else"],"sources":["bblocks://usgin.bbr.geosci.gsmEarthMaterial"],"keyword":"else"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","16"],"title":"p","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","16","type"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15"],"title":"o","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","bbox"]},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","geometries"],"required":true,"schema_type":"array"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","geometries","type"],"required":true,"schema_type":"string"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","measures"]},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","coordRefSys"]},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","15","type"],"required":true,"const":"MultiSurface"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","14"],"title":"n","keyword":"branch"},{"path":["_then","features","place","_oneOf","14","bbox"]},{"path":["_